      • runMain

        public static boolean runMain(java.io.File submission,
                              java.io.File input,
                              java.lang.String regex)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Runs the main method of the file given with the input and checks if it matches the regular expression given.

        Only works on files with a main method. Ideally, this should only be run on files whose methods have been replaced but general content was written by intructor. Does still work for student submission, but calling this method on a raw student submission doesn't fit the intended grading workflow

        Parameters:
        submission - work to be run
        input - input given to main method, can be null if no input is needed
        regex - regular expression to match the output with
        Returns:
        true if file runs successfully and the output matches the regular expression, false otherwise
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - any exception
